reviews.text: So lovely! They were so kind to let us in outside of open hours. Remarkable art.

Wonderful museum in a beautiful building.  I've visited many times and the new indoor sculpture gallery is a highlight.  You won't be disappointed. They also have a great staff and wonderful docents to help explain the exhibits and the history of the region.

Have been twice. The art was high quality and they had some famous artists as well as some regional ones too. The staff was kind and helpful. I was on my honeymoon the second time I went and they gave us free admission. The souvenir shop is neat as well. I'd recommend dropping by if you're in the area.
A must see. Really enjoyed myself
Great place to visit.  Beautiful facility and great run out to listen to Joe B. Davis, President of Former Texas Rangers Association.

I would have given a five but my steak was so spicy my husband had to eat it. Having said that I want to say how wonderful the staff and owner was. They were delightful. The salad was amazing as was the potato skins. Although I would not consider those appetizers.  They are a meal into themselves.  Soooo good. The Texas toast was delicious as well. One funny thing that I really enjoyed was the orange slice on the plate. The best orange I have had in a long time. I had some of my husbands steak and it was tender and juicy. We will definitely be back. We were too full to have dessert but it all looked good.

My first time and I was amazed!!! Not only did the resteraunt mgr greet us, he provided a tour of the restaurant to give us a view of how unique this place really is! Looks like a nice lounge there as well!! So the restaurant has a nice warm, cozy feeling to it. 
SUPERB CUSTOMER SERVICE!!! 

Great wine selection and the steaks were REALLY prepared well!! But save room for their dessert... I had their chocolate cake with fudge!!
This just might be the best steak I ever had. Each bite was tender and flavorful. Cooked to perfection.  The staff is friendly and service is excellent. We felt right at home! I recommend it!

Being new to the area, we found the Cowboy Steak House great ! From the service to the food....5 star....Outstanding.
And that's off to Lorie 3, great service.
Thankyou.
Great food, great staff; very friendly. Met 2 other couples from same home state(Iowa) and had a fun time.
U love this place. Veteran owned. Older decor but very clean. Good place for your budget too.
Very  nice...Large clean roomsI highly recommend  staying here.
This was one of the cleanest hotels we have ever stayed at. Owner was very nice and the bed was. Dry comfortable.
Will not stay anywhere else after this trip. Svend & Rachelle are wonderful. Never been treated better.Highly recommend staying here!!

The couple that runs this place are wonderful! The rooms are nothing special but they are clean and comfortable. The owners even put towels on our motorcycle in the morning. Very thoughtful. We will come back to stay here in the future!

Our motorcycle group booked a dining room for our Christmas Party. Friday is the Prime Rib dinner buffet and there was about 18 couples at the event. We all enjoyed the $19pp buffet and the restaurant assigned two servers who did a great job keeping the tables happy.

Excellent food and staff.  Might be the best prime rib I've ever eaten.  One small complaint,  the seafood chowder used some of that fake processed seafood stuff..it was not good in a soup because it was mushy.

The service was absolutely horrible. I very rarely compliane but I did here after waiting 15 minutes for my check and another 10 at the counter to pay. Staff seemed very untrained and very slow. The food was pretty good but not good enough for me to return.
Yum. Friday buffet delicious. Pretty place. Short on waitresses but still service was very nice.

Beautiful restaurant in the YO hotel. We always go on Saturday nights. They have a great buffet at a reasonable price. We love the ranch atmosphere of the hotel and the food is very good. Highly recommend.
It's edible, not gross or anything. The food used to be delicious. This is my second time in 2016 to be extremely disappointed. Canned chicken, really?
This is more than good Mexican food. It's creative cooking passed down through the family, made with love & served with pleasure.
Excellent local food, made fresh to order, and always done right!
Really good food. If you're in the area, I highly recommend that you stop by here.
First time to visit, and will be back. Great food - thoughtfully prepared. Lots of regulars.

They are OPEN, my wife and I stopped in yesterday, (March 13, 2015). She had a JD Coke and said it was a good mix. I had a couple beers, nobody can screw that up. We also had some Mozzarella Sticks, no complains there. The lady bartender was very courteous and friendly, we had some questions, she answer them all. Total cost $17 plus change, that did not seem out of line. We will definitely be return customers.

Been here 2 times... drinks are good. Beer can't mess that up.... but the food was horrible and it took forever to get food out. Music was alright... started great with some classic country hits but then took a turn for the worse when they played nothing but Kenny Rogers for 30 mins. Zzzzz
Went there on a Sunday afternoon, looking for live music.  No live music on a Sunday, but the bartender was great fun.  Kept us entertained and laughing.  An overall good experience.

Okay, I haven't been there in a while and I heard there is new ownership, but I don't know. When I was there I paid top dollar for what tasted, smelt and had the texture of what would come from a microwave dinner. The chicken was dry, and flavorless. OKay and my one all time favorite dessert, Tiramisu, I have had nothing like it. When you go to what is supposed to be a fine dining establishment that offers tiramisu as a dessert, and you are like me, your heart kinda skips a beat with anticipation. Well my one hope after the food like substance we were served for the main course was, hopefully the tiramisu will be good. I shoulda known better, They brought me a pre made still semi frozen slab of crap. Either make it there or don't bother.
K sorry, I'm done now.

over priced.  the food was not very good (though it did look fancy).  I have eaten there twice, both times i left feeling cheated.   service was good, atmosphere was ok, but kinda uptight and touristy.

Love this place! Anytime I'm in the area, it's a must. I enjoy going on Wednesday's for the chicken fried steak lunch special. Great prices and the portions will actually fill you up. I've never had an issue with the service. The waitresses are all very friendly. I recommend for a quick bite on a lunch break.
Love this restaurant and the people who own it. I haven't ever been unhappy with a single meal I have had there. It is almost as good as being at Memaw's.
Always a great place to eat. In fact, when I was younger I even recall when my Grandpa and I would eat here almost weekly. Keep up the great work guys your absolutely amazing.
Perfectly cooked bacon, grits and eggs. Great coffee, clean establishment and friendly staff.
We had the pork chop special 😋 and it was great meal 👌 home made mashed potatoes and gravy and cabbage and carrots and soup it was the bom
